    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Jany 1854. 5614</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>239 Tenth Street</placeName></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My dear sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Having relinquished my clerical ap&#45;<lb/>pointment in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>&#44; I have come hither for the purpose<lb/> of engaging my services in the <placeName>U. S.</placeName> in the same sacred<lb/> calling. I possess Testimonials of the highest nature as a<lb/> Hazan&#44; Preacher and Teacher. Previous to my departure I<lb/> had the additional satisfaction of receiving Two Public<lb/> addresses&#44; one emanating from my former congr. of Spanish<lb/> Town&#44; and the other from the entire Jewish Community of<lb/> <placeName>Kingston</placeName>. A copy of the latter I now enclose&#44; and may I<lb/> request the kind insertion of the same in the &#8220;Occident&#8221; together<lb/> with any remarks which may prove serviceable to me in<lb/> this country. For this act I will feel grateful particularly<lb/> as I am a candidate for the vacant office of Minister of<lb/> the Portuguese Kahal of <placeName>Richmond Va</placeName>. The <persName>Revd. Mr Isaacs</persName><lb/> has promised to use his influence for me in that quarter&#44;<lb/> and if it would not be taxing your friendship too much&#44;<lb/> a letter from you to any influential party there would be<lb/> material in forwarding my views.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With God&#39;s blessing I will call to see<lb/> you shortly as I have much to say to you. The Occident<lb/> is scarcely seen in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>&#44; and were it not for the</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>kindness of <persName>Mr Delevante</persName>&#44; who occasionally lent me<lb/> a no. I should have been in a similar plight.<lb/> Possibly I may suggest some method of promoting a<lb/> better circulation of so excellent a Mag. In <placeName>Kingston</placeName>. I<lb/> paid <persName>Miss S. C. Peixotto</persName> &#36;3.25 for my subscription for one<lb/> year&#59; since the period which this embraces I do not think<lb/> I have received six nos. However we will converse<lb/> further on the subject.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">With my best respects</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Yours faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Jacobs</persName>.</p>
			<p>In your remarks&#44; would you notify<lb/> that I am a Pupil of the <persName>Revd. Isaac Lopez</persName><lb/> and have from him a Certificate of Efficiency<lb/> as a <hi rend="underline">Portuguese</hi> Reader&#63;</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><date>1&#45;13&#45;1854C</date></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>Prepaid</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p>pmail</p>
          
